# tf-mod-aws-endpoints

## Module description


Use the `tf-mod-aws-endpoints` Terraform module to provision an [`Endpoint`](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/rande.html) for any AWS service




Project: **[%!s(<nil>)](%!s(<nil>))** : [[%!s(<nil>)](%!s(<nil>))] | [[%!s(<nil>)](%!s(<nil>))]

## Usage

**IMPORTANT:** The `master` branch is used in `source` just as an example. In your code, do not pin to `master` because there may be breaking changes between releases.
Instead pin to the release tag (e.g. `?ref=tags/x.y.z`) of one of our [latest releases](https://github.com/https://github.com/Callumccr/tf-mod-aws-endpoints/releases).


The below values shown in the usage of this module are purely representative, please replace desired values as required.
